    {
      "_id": "cb4fe4f4f35d6275",
      "name": "Health Thresholds",
      "sort": 4,
      "text": {
        "content": "<p id=\"2be1b90a-e081-80fa-a094-e91d5aba95d0\" class=\"block-color-default_background\">Certain game mechanics affect creatures while their current HP is within certain thresholds. These HP thresholds are determined before any temporary changes to your HP maximum, such as from the <strong>Doomed </strong>Condition.</p><ul id=\"2be1b90a-e081-8088-b4a8-df78f4db5cd4\" class=\"bulleted-list\"><li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><em><strong>Bloodied:</strong></em> HP is equal to or lower than 1/2 its maximum HP.</li></ul><ul id=\"2be1b90a-e081-80a6-b1cb-f7df9b0e2c00\" class=\"bulleted-list\"><li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><em><strong>Well-Bloodied:</strong></em> HP is equal to or lower than 1/4 its maximum HP.</li></ul><ul id=\"2be1b90a-e081-80e5-aedd-d0e11efb4ce1\" class=\"bulleted-list\"><li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><em><strong>Death’s Door:</strong></em> HP is equal to or lower than 0 HP, to a minimum of its Death Threshold.</li></ul><p id=\"2be1b90a-e081-8034-9860-c8d57741991d\" class=\"block-color-default_background\">A creature’s Death Threshold is equal to 0 HP minus its Prime Modifier and its Combat Mastery.</p><p id=\"2be1b90a-e081-809c-a13c-fe143f87f930\" class=\"block-color-purple_background\"><strong>DC Tip:</strong> If a creature is on Death’s Door, they are still considered to be Bloodied and Well-Bloodied, because their HP is still below 1/2 their maximum (Bloodied) and 1/4 their maximum (Well-Bloodied).</p><p id=\"2be1b90a-e081-803e-a652-e9a4a408c062\" class=\"block-color-blue_background\"><strong>Example:</strong> A creature with a maximum HP of 8 is considered Bloodied when its HP is 4 or lower, Well-Bloodied when its HP is 2 or lower, and on Death’s Door when its HP is 0 or lower. If its Prime Modifier is 3 and its Combat Mastery is 1, the creature’s Death Threshold is <strong>-4 HP</strong>. That creature dies if its HP is ever reduced to <strong>-4 HP</strong> or lower.</p>",
        "format": 1
      },
